"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-summer-olympics-medal-count-live-updates-french-games\", \"text\": \"The2024 Paris Olympicsare wrapped up.  While there were an overwhelming number of sports and athletes to follow, a sweeping glance at the Games always brings us back to the core of it all: medals.  For almost all events, gold, silver and bronze medals are awarded to the winner, runner-up and the second runner-up, respectively. Two bronze medals are awards in boxing, judo, taekwondo and  wrestling. Medals have been awarded since 1896, and the 1904 Games in St. Louis were the first Games to feature the now-colloquial gold, silver, bronze hierarchy.  One note: Team sports do not multiply the count of total medals. Those still count as just one medal.  RELATED:Everything to Know About Olympic Medals and What Athletes in Paris Win  Country  Total  Gold  Silver  Bronze  United States  126  40  44  42  China  91  40  27  24  Japan  45  20  12  13  Australia  53  18  19  16  France*  64  16  26  22  Netherlands  34  15  7  12  Great Britain  65  14  22  29  South Korea  32  13  9  10  Italy  40  12  13  15  Germany  33  12  13  8  New Zealand  20  10  7  3  Canada  27  9  7  11  Uzbekistan  13  8  2  3  Hungary  19  6  7  6  Spain  18  5  4  9  Sweden  11  4  4  3  Kenya  11  4  2  5  Norway  8  4  1  3  Ireland  7  4  0  3  Brazil  20  3  7  10  Iran  12  3  6  3  Ukraine  12  3  5  4  Romania  9  3  4  2  Georgia  7  3  3  1  Belgium  10  3  1  6  Bulgaria  7  3  1  3  Serbia  5  3  1  1  Czech Republic  5  3  0  2  Denmark  9  2  2  5  Azerbaijan  7  2  2  3  Croatia  7  2  2  3  Cuba  9  2  1  6  Bahrain  4  2  1  1  Slovenia  3  2  1  0  Chinese Taipei  7  2  0  5  Austria  5  2  0  3  Hong Kong  4  2  0  2  Philippines  4  2  0  2  Algeria  3  2  0  1  Indonesia  3  2  0  1  Israel  7  1  5  1  Poland  10  1  4  5  Kazakhstan  7  1  3  3  Jamaica  6  1  3  2  South Africa  6  1  3  2  Thailand  6  1  3  2  Individual Neutral Athletes[A][B]  5  1  3  1  Ethiopia  4  1